-----------------------------------------------------------------------
COMMAND-LINE VERSION

Unpack the archive using zip (WinZip, etc.)  Change to the Treasure
directory.  To generate a treasure, type:

    python Treasure.py A

where the A represents the treasure type A-Z.  Alternately, you may 
specify one of MAGIC, POTION, SCROLL, RING, WAND, ROD, STAFF, MISC,
ARMOR, or WEAPON to generate one magic item at random.  Lowercase is
changed to uppercase automatically, so

    python Treasure.py Magic

is OK.  Output is written to stdout, so you can say:

    python Treasure.py h >dragon-hoard.txt

to save the output in a text file.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
WEB-ENABLED VERSION

Put the Treasure directory in your /usr/home/httpd/htdocs (or wherever
your webserver home directory is) and use a URL like this:

    http://your.server.org/Treasure/treasure.cgi

to get the web-enabled version.  You may have to change the shebang 
(#!) info at the top of the treasure.cgi file to correctly point to 
your Python interpreter, and you may need to configure your webserver 
to allow execution in that folder; webserver setup is up to you.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

